cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with tracking mobile objects in different scene conditions using computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of Kalman filter and trajectory filtering, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems, indicating a possible fit with cs.RO (Robotics). The use of multiple feature similarity measures and the absence of prior knowledge information suggest a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as clustering and classification, indicating a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed algorithm against other state-of-the-art algorithms, indicating a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning).
